      "explanation": "$100 = 14 \\cdot 7 + 2$, so $100 \\bmod 7 = 2$.",
      "difficulty": "medium",
      "steps": [
        {
          "text": "**Strategy: find the LARGEST multiple of 7 that fits in 100.** Then $100 \\bmod 7$ is what's left over."
        },
        {
          "text": "**Find the multiple.** $14 \\cdot 7 = 98$. (Next one is $15 \\cdot 7 = 105$ — too big.)"
        },
        {
          "text": "**Subtract.** $100 - 98 = 2$."
        },
        {
          "text": "**Result.** $100 \\bmod 7 = 2$. (The 'remainder' meaning: after fitting 14 sevens into 100, you have 2 left over.)"
        }
      ]
