      "explanation": "Digit sum $4+5+2+7 = 18$, which IS divisible by 9. So $4527$ is divisible by 9. Verify: $4527 / 9 = 503$. ✓",
      "difficulty": "medium",
      "steps": [
        {
          "text": "**Divisibility-by-9 rule.** A number is divisible by 9 IFF the SUM OF ITS DIGITS is divisible by 9. (Same trick for 3.)"
        },
        {
          "text": "**Apply.** Digit sum of 4527: $4 + 5 + 2 + 7 = 18$."
        },
        {
          "text": "**Check.** $18 = 2 \\cdot 9$ ✓ — divisible by 9. So 4527 IS divisible by 9."
        },
        {
          "text": "**Verify with division.** $4527 / 9 = 503$ exactly ✓."
        },
        {
          "text": "**Why the digit-sum trick works.** Each power of 10 satisfies $10^k \\equiv 1 \\pmod 9$. So any number written in base 10 is congruent to its digit sum mod 9. Neat consequence of modular arithmetic."
        }
      ]
    }
